r/src/jobs/sync.ts`** (line 48): calls `createUser(input)`\n\nBoth should use `registerUser` instead.\n\n#### Breakage 3: Broken tsconfig Project References (Build Order)\n\n**`/workspace/tsconfig.json`** lists references in this order:\n```json\n\"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" }\n]\n```\n\nSince both `api` and `worker` depend on `core` (as declared in their own `tsconfig.json` references), `core` must be listed first:\n```json\n\"references\": [\n    { \"path\": \"packages/core\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/api\" },\n    { \"path\": \"packages/worker\" }\n]\n```\n\n#### Breakage 4: Dependency Version Conflict (zod)\n\n**`/workspace/packages/core/package.json`** (line 12) pins `zod` to version `3.19.0`:\n```json\n\"zod\": \"3.19.0\"\n```\n\nHowever, **`/workspace/packages/core/src/validation.ts`** uses `z.pipe()` (lines 20-22, 28-29, 33-34) and `z.coerce` -- features that were introduced in zod 3.22. The file's own comment at line 3 states: \"Uses z.pipe() for string-to-number coercion (requires zod >= 3.22).\" The pinned version 3.19.0 is too old for these APIs.\n\n#### Breakage 5: Merge Conflict Markers\n\n**`/workspace/packages/api/tests/users.test.ts`** (lines 14-28) contains unresolved merge conflict markers:\n```typescript\n<<<<<<< HEAD\n  it('creates user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n=======\n  it('registers user with valid data', async () => {\n    const res = await request(app)\n      .post('/users')\n      .set('x-user-role', 'admin')\n      .send({ name: 'Test', email: 'test@test.com', role: 'user' });\n    expect(res.status).toBe(201);\n>>>>>>> refactor/user-system\n```\n\nThe \"incoming\" side (refactor branch) is the correct version since it sends the required `role`